(432,	9,	'2016-07-18 22:04:40',	'2016-07-18 22:04:40',	'<h1>The Adaptable Mind</h1>\r\n<p class=\"p-bold\">The film is available with subtitles in Arabic, Chinese, English captions, French, German, Hebrew, Hindi, Russian, Spanish, and Swahili.</p>\r\nThe Adaptable Mind (11 mins) explores the skills we need to flourish in the 21st Century. It is one of the featured films for this upcoming Character Day on September 22nd, 2016. It was just selected by the US State Department as part of their American Film Showcase, where they send films and filmmakers around the world to represent the US and foster dialogue across borders. The film premiered last year in over 6700 classrooms, schools, and organizations in 41 countries for Character Day 2015\r\n\r\nWe hope you\'ll join us for Character Day 2016!\r\n<p class=\"p-bold\">Resource Hub:</p>\r\nDive deeper into these ideas with thousands of resources including lesson plans, discussion guides, research, websites, books, films, and more. Discussion Guides and Lesson Plans for The Adaptable Mind are available here.\r\n\r\n<a class=\"buttonA\" href=\"#\">CONTRIBUTE</a>    <a class=\"buttonA\" href=\"#\">TRANSLATE</a>',	'Adaptable Mind',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'122-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2016-07-18 22:04:40',	'2016-07-18 22:04:40',	'',	122,	'http://www.letitripple.dreamhosters.com/2016/07/18/122-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(435,	9,	'2016-08-03 23:31:44',	'2016-08-03 23:31:44',	'The Science of Character (8 mins) explores the neuroscience and social science that proves that we can shape who we are, and who we want to be in the world. The film is one of the <a href=\"http://www.letitripple.org/films/\">featured films</a> for Character Day on September 22nd where over 26,000 groups around the world will be screening the film, joining our global online Q&amp;A, delving into our discussion materials to catalyze deeper conversations about character development. <a href=\"http://www.letitripple.org/character-day\">Join us</a>.\n\nThe film is available with subtitles in Spanish, Chinese, French, German, Arabic, Hebrew, Hindi, Russian, and Swahili.\n\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-918 aligncenter\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/02132059/Periodic-Table-Poster.jpg\" alt=\"Periodic Table Poster\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" />\n\n<a href=\"http://the-moxie-institute-film-studio.myshopify.com/products/the-science-of-character-poster\">Purchase</a> or <a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/02132059/Periodic-Table-Poster.jpg\">Download file</a>\n<h2>Order Your Discussion Kit That Coincides with The Science of Character Film</h2>\nThese kits are the perfect resource to get discussions circulating around the film and diving deeper into what makes us human. Each kit contains a poster of the Periodic Table of Character Strengths and also includes a deck of 44 discussion cards. Kits are free to the first 13,000 groups that order them (however, must cover shipping and handling).\n\nOrder now\n\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-1012 aligncenter\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/03220950/SOC-Sign-Up.png\" alt=\"SOC-Sign-Up\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" />\n<h2>This film was inspired by the work of:</h2>\nMartin Seligman, Christopher Peterson, Carol Dweck, Angela Duckworth, David Levin, Paul Tough, Dominic Randolph, Neal Mayerson, Adele Diamond, Clifford Nass, The Bezos Family Foundation, The Character Lab, The VIA Institute on Character, Common Sense Media, and many more.',	'Science of Character',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'126-autosave-v1',	'',	'',	'2016-08-03 23:31:44',	'2016-08-03 23:31:44',	'',	126,	'http://www.letitripple.dreamhosters.com/2016/07/18/126-autosave-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
