(600,	1,	'2016-07-23 05:30:18',	'2016-07-23 05:30:18',	'<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-685\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/24224514/Mensch_Bread.png\" alt=\"Mensch_Bread\" width=\"708\" height=\"397\" />\r\n\r\nFilmmaker Tiffany Shlain’s nonprofit Let it Ripple will broaden the reach of its Character Day, which uses film and discussion materials to create a global conversation about the importance of character-building in today’s 24/7 world.\r\n\r\nCharacter Day – described as “an annual global day devoted to developing who we are and who we want to be in the world” – will be celebrated worldwide on Sept. 22.\r\n\r\nRead more here',	'Character Day in Arizona Jewish News',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'open',	'',	'learning-from-boardroom-perspectives-on-leader-character-4',	'',	'',	'2016-08-02 11:09:58',	'2016-08-02 11:09:58',	'',	0,	'http://www.letitripple.dreamhosters.com/2016/07/23/learning-from-boardroom-perspectives-on-leader-character-4/',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(601,	1,	'2016-07-23 06:00:41',	'2016-07-23 06:00:41',	'<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-939\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/02220738/Screen-Shot-2016-08-02-at-3.07.19-PM.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2016-08-02 at 3.07.19 PM\" width=\"387\" height=\"126\" />\r\n<h2>\"Character Day 2016 Poised to Reach Millions in Global Conversation\"</h2>\r\nBuilding on the global success and momentum of Character Day 2015, in which hundreds of thousands participated and viewed the films “The Making of a Mensch” and “The Adaptable Mind,” Emmy-nominated filmmaker Tiffany Shlain’s nonprofit “Let it Ripple” this year will broaden the initiative’s reach that uses film and discussion materials to create a global conversation about the importance of character-building in today’s 24/7 world—developing strengths like creativity, humility, grit, courage, compassion and empathy.\r\n\r\n<a class=\"buttonA\" href=\"http://jewishlinkbwc.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;id=7981%3Acharacter-day-2016-poised-to-reach-millions-in-global-conversation&amp;Itemid=584\">Read more here</a>',	'Character Day in The Jewish Link',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'open',	'',	'learning-from-boardroom-perspectives-on-leader-character-5',	'',	'',	'2016-08-02 23:54:41',	'2016-08-02 23:54:41',	'',	0,	'http://www.letitripple.dreamhosters.com/2016/07/23/learning-from-boardroom-perspectives-on-leader-character-5/',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(602,	1,	'2016-07-24 03:38:01',	'2016-07-24 03:38:01',	'<img class=\"wp-image-675 aligncenter\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/24220701/CharacterDayLogo.jpg\" alt=\"CharacterDayLogo\" width=\"401\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\nIt seems these days that our Character is being tested -- individually, as a country, and across the world -- and it\'s been so moving to see how many schools, companies, organizations and congregations have signed up to join our 3rd annual Character Day set for Sept 22nd. We would love to have you <a href=\"http://www.characterday.org\">join us.</a>\r\n\r\nNow in its third year, Character Day is a free global initiative where groups around the world screen films on the science of character development from different perspectives, dive into printed discussion materials, and join an online global conversation around character (importance of strengths like empathy, courage, grit, kindness) -- all rooted in evidence-based research.\r\n\r\nHere are some exciting updates:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Over 20,000 events in 40 countries are already signed up for Sept 22.</strong> <a href=\"http://www.characterday.org\">Read more</a>, find specific <a href=\"http://www.letitripple.org/character-day#suggestedevents\">ideas for your group</a>, and <strong>sign up here</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Over 75 entire school districts are participating. </strong>That means every school in those districts, including DC Public Schools, Oakland Unified, San Francisco Unified, and LA Unified.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Companies are joining. </strong>Professional development, HR departments, summits, retreats, lunches...all the perfect place for Character Day.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Rabbis, Educators, Museums, and JCCs across the country</strong> are making screening plans for The Making of a Mensch. A great way to prepare for high holidays.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a class=\"buttonA\" href=\"https://t.e2ma.net/message/van03/n87sfs\">Read more here</a>',	'Character Day July Newsletter',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'open',	'',	'learning-from-boardroom-perspectives-on-leader-character-6',	'',	'',	'2016-08-03 00:42:21',	'2016-08-03 00:42:21',	'',	0,	'http://www.letitripple.dreamhosters.com/2016/07/23/learning-from-boardroom-perspectives-on-leader-character-6/',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
