(623,	9,	'2016-07-24 18:24:14',	'2016-07-24 18:24:14',	'<h1>The Making of a Mensch</h1>\r\nThe Making of a Mensch is available with subtitles in Arabic, Chinese, English Captions, French, German, Hebrew, Hindi, Russian, Spanish, and Swahili.\r\n<h2><strong>Join us for Character Day 2016!</strong></h2>\r\nJoin over 20,000 events around the world for our 3rd annual Character Day, when schools, classrooms, congregations, and organizations in over 40 countries will be screening The Making of a Mensch, as well as other films exploring character education from different perspectives. We provide the films, discussion kits, and a global online conversation (all generously supported by grants, at no cost to you). You create an event that works for your community. <strong>Find out more and sign up here</strong>.\r\n<h2><strong>About The Film</strong></h2>\r\nThis 10 min film and accompanying discussion kit explore character education through the wonderful ancient Jewish teachings of Mussar. The film and materials explore the ideas and practices through through an engaging and accessible lens, reminding us all how relevant these Jewish tools are to our 21st century lives.\r\n\r\nThe film premiered as part of <strong>Character Day</strong> (Sept 18), a global day with films, resources, and conversation about who we are, who we want to be in the world, and how we can get there.\r\n<h2><strong>Discussion Materials</strong></h2>\r\nYou can order a hands-on discussion kit, download the kit, and dive into lesson plans and <strong>thousands of resources here</strong>. We will be launching an even more robust resource hub on Character Day 2016.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-622\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/24182352/The_Mensch_Kit_1.jpg\" alt=\"The_Mensch_Kit_1\" width=\"650\" height=\"506\" />\r\n\r\nThis discussion kit was made possible by funds granted by <strong>The Covenant Foundation</strong>, Lippman Kanfer Foundation for Living Torah, the Natan Fund, and others.\r\n<h2><strong>Press</strong></h2>\r\nThere was a special live premiere screening at <strong>The JCCSF Arts &amp; Ideas</strong> on Friday Sept 18th at 7:30pm. Director Tiffany Shlain was interviewed after the screening by Michael Krasny (KQED Forum). <strong>Click here to watch the interview</strong>.\r\n\r\nRead our <strong>Press Release</strong>.\r\n\r\nRead <strong>Participant Testimonials and Press Highlights Here</strong>.',	'Making of a Mensch',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'124-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2016-07-24 18:24:14',	'2016-07-24 18:24:14',	'',	124,	'http://www.letitripple.dreamhosters.com/2016/07/24/124-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
