(881,	9,	'2016-06-09 11:35:39',	'2016-06-09 11:35:39',	'<h2><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-882\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/02113928/Politico-Logo.jpg\" alt=\"POLITICO NO LINES\" width=\"1696\" height=\"525\" /></h2>\r\n<h2>LET’S TALK ABOUT CHARACTER:</h2>\r\nStudents, parents and teachers across the country are getting ready for summer vacation, but Emmy-nominated filmmaker and Webby Awards Founder Tiffany Shlain is gearing up for back to school. She’s working furiously to engage thousands of students and schools in Character Day on September 22. The day is meant to celebrate character development and character strengths. On the first Character Day in 2014, more than 1,500 events were held by schools and organizations that showed short films and talked to students about how to live fulfilling and meaningful lives. Shlain told Morning Education that the number of events this year has already swelled to 10,000. <a href=\"https://content.govdelivery.com/accounts/USED/bulletins/145ae06\">The Education Department</a>, the State Department, Common Sense Media, Edutopia, The Teachers Guild, Class Dojo, Character Counts, Character.org and others are getting involved.\r\n\r\n<a class=\"buttonA\" href=\"http://www.politico.com/tipsheets/morning-education/2016/06/senate-grilling-over-title-ix-guidance-214734#ixzz4B75kVHex\">Read more here</a>',	'Character Day Featured in Politico Education Round-up',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'open',	'',	'character-day-featured-in-politico-education-round-up',	'',	'',	'2016-08-02 11:40:28',	'2016-08-02 11:40:28',	'',	0,	'http://www.letitripple.org/?p=881',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
