ow-the-internet-is-shaping-our\">Harvard Business Review: How the Internet is Shaping Our “Global Brain”</a>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/22211009/Screen-Shot-2016-07-22-at-12.32.18-PM.jpg\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2016-07-22 at 12.32.18 PM\" width=\"650\" height=\"190\" />\r\n\r\nTiffany has just begun production directing on a short film on women and power that will be released by <a href=\"http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/kristen-stewart-directorial-debut-refinery29-889616\">Refinery29</a> in the fall.',	'Tiffany Shlain',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'98-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2016-08-02 12:06:40',	'2016-08-02 12:06:40',	'',	98,	'http://www.letitripple.org/2016/08/02/98-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(894,	9,	'2016-08-02 12:08:10',	'2016-08-02 12:08:10',	'<h1>The Adaptable Mind</h1>\r\nThe film is available with subtitles in Arabic, Chinese, English captions, French, German, Hebrew, Hindi, Russian, Spanish, and Swahili.\r\n\r\nThe Adaptable Mind (11 mins) explores the skills we need to flourish in the 21st Century. It is one of the featured films for this upcoming Character Day on September 22nd, 2016. It was just selected by the US State Department as part of their American Film Showcase, where they send films and filmmakers around the world to represent the US and foster dialogue across borders. The film premiered last year in over 6700 classrooms, schools, and organizations in 41 countries for <strong>Character Day 2015</strong>\r\n\r\nWe hope you\'ll join us for <strong>Character Day 2016!</strong>\r\n<h2 class=\"p-bold\">Resource Hub</h2>\r\nDive deeper into these ideas with thousands of resources including lesson plans, discussion guides, research, websites, books, films, and more. <strong>Discussion Guides and Lesson Plans for The Adaptable Mind are available here</strong>.',	'Adaptable Mind',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'122-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2016-08-02 12:08:10',	'2016-08-02 12:08:10',	'',	122,	'http://www.letitripple.org/2016/08/02/122-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(895,	9,	'2016-08-02 12:19:07',	'2016-08-02 12:19:07',	'<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">HIGHLIGHTS FROM CHARACTER DAY 2015</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>6,784 screenings at schools, classrooms, workplaces, and organizations.</li>\r\n 	<li>Events were held in 41 countries, on all inhabited continents. (There wasn\'t one in Antarctica this year;)</li>\r\n 	<li>People from over 125 countries tapped into the conversation online.</li>\r\n 	<li>Over 35 million Twitter and press impressions and engagements.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://blog.ed.gov/2015/09/celebrate-character-day/\">US Sec of Education Arne Duncan\'s great article about Character Day</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.theatlantic.com/education/archive/2015/09/civic-education-citizenship-test/405889/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-897 aligncenter\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/02121247/HBR_logo_gray.png\" alt=\"HBR_logo_gray\" width=\"200\" height=\"112\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.theatlantic.com/education/archive/2015/09/civic-education-citizenship-test/405889/\"><img class=\"wp-image-899 aligncenter\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/02121315/theatlantic.png\" alt=\"theatlantic\" width=\"201\" height=\"66\" /></a> <a href=\"https://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/what-matters-most/201509/top-10-amazing-recent-findings-character-strengths\"><img class=\"wp-image-898 aligncenter\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/02121256/Psychology-Today-Logo.gif\" alt=\"Psychology-Today-Logo\" width=\"201\" height=\"65\" /></a> <img class=\"alignnone wp-image-900 aligncenter\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/letitripple-media/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/02121349/usatoday.png\" alt=\"usatoday\" width=\"199\" height=\"125\" /><a href=\"https://hbr.org/ideacast/2015/09/build-your-character-at-least-for-a-day.html\">\r\n</a>\r\n...and many more!</p>\r\n<img cla